  "title": "Abortive Infection Mechanisms and Prophage Sequences Significantly Influence the Genetic Makeup of Emerging Lytic Lactococcal Phages",
  "summary": "The study describes the evolution of lytic lactococcal phages (ul36 and its mutants) through recombination with the inducible prophage φsmq86 in Lactococcus lactis. The phages exhibit genome plasticity, varying genome sizes, GC content, and morphological differences, particularly in tail length and baseplate structure. They show resistance to AbiK and AbiT systems, with significant genomic modifications.",
